name: IOSPP - International Organisation for School Prefects and Presidents
tag_list: social-network, education, high-school, secondary-school, head-boy, prefects, school-assembly, hall-monitors
overview:
IOSPP is a private social network for Schools where Head Boys, Head Girls, Prefects and students in similar leadership positions can network safely.

IOSPP was launched on December 2011.

IOSPP - The International Organisation for School Prefects and Presidents, is a community designed to encourage students in leadership roles at the school such as presidents, head boys, house captains or class representatives.

This is a private Social Network accessible only by the students and teachers of the schools suscribed through the site www.iospp.org.

IOSPP connects pupils with similar profiles and interests around the world, giving them the chance to interact, exchange ideas, experiences and find opportunities to participate in international events representing their schools or applying for scholarships.
